    "Commentary Vol. 50": "The likeness of anything that creepeth on the ground, etc.] As\nserpents by many; and indeed that creature is introduced into almost all the\nidolatries of the Heathens, which seems to take its rise from the serpent\nSatan made use of to deceive our first parents:\nthe likeness of any fish that is in the waters beneath the earth; as the\ncrocodile and hippopotamus, or river horse, by the Egyptians; and Dagon\n56\nand Derceto, supposed to be figures in the form of a fish, among the\nPhoenicians.\nVer."
