    "Mark Allan Powell, Mark E. Biddle, Martin Luther": "). YHWH alone presides over the fates of all nations,\nnot just over Israel. YHWH is Lord over the Amorites displaced by\nIsrael because of their sin just as YHWH is Lord over the\nBabylonians who take Israel captive because of its sin. Israel should,\ntherefore, pause to consider the significance of its experiences of\nYHWH and acknowledge that YHWH is God both in heaven and\nover all the earth.\nCoupled with this interest in asserting a strict monotheism, this\npassage (especially"
